[
  {
    "text": "♪ instrumental hip hop music ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hello, I am Dominik ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I am thrilled to introduce you to Swift Charts, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple's new framework for making informative ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "and delightful charts in SwiftUI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "Data surrounds us and provides an unprecedented resource ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "for understanding the world and making better decisions. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "Yet, data alone is of little use. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "To make data useful, we must make sense of it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "A well-designed and accessible data visualization ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "can clearly communicate complex data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "and turn data into understanding and knowledge. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "At Apple, we spent years studying the best practices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "for visualizations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "We learned that charts work best ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "when they show additional useful context around data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "like the trends and fluctuations of stock prices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "over some time range, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "your heart rate during the last workout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "and when the day will cool off in the evening. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "And these are just some of the many examples ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "across all our platforms where we use charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, I'm excited to introduce you to a new framework ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can make informative and delightful charts in your apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "Say hello to Swift Charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts is a flexible framework ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "for making Apple-designed charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "It uses the same declarative syntax as SwiftUI, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you already know the language of Swift Charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "So today, let's make some informative, accessible, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "and delightful visualizations with Swift Charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the team, we've been helping ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "a pop-up pancake food truck track its sales with an app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "The truck serves an international variety ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "of sweet and savory pancakes like cachapa, injera, crêpe, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=122"
  },
  {
    "text": "jian bing, dosa, or American pancakes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "The food truck served more than 4500 pancakes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "across these styles in the last 30 days. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "Cachapa were the most popular and the app already shows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=143"
  },
  {
    "text": "the most important information in the title. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's add a chart to show a detailed breakdown ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the six pancakes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=155"
  },
  {
    "text": "To make this visualization in Swift Charts, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can use the same declarative syntax as SwiftUI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Swift Charts, you build charts by composition. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "The main components of a bar chart are the bars, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "which are visual elements for each item in your data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts calls these visual elements \"marks.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's jump into Xcode to make this chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "We start with adding a chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "To make a bar, I add a BarMark inside the Chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "To show a bar for the number of cachapas, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "we have to set the name and the sales.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "We set the x-position of the bar to be derived from the value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=203"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the name of pancake -- in this case \"Cachapa.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=207"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first argument to the .value factory method ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the description of the value, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the second is the value itself. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "And now we get a single bar in the preview. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "The height of each bar described by the y attribute ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "should be set by the number of cachapas sold, which were 916. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "To indicate that we're not setting the position ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "or height of the bar directly, we use .value. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=238"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts automatically creates not only the bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "but also a label for the bars on the x-axis ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=247"
  },
  {
    "text": "and a y-axis that shows what the length of a bar means. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's add a second bar for injera, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "of which the truck sold 850.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=259"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, it's cool to build individual marks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=264"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see them appear in the app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, we usually want to create a chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "driven by a collection such as an array of structs. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll start by adding a struct for my pancake sales.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "It has a name -- which is a string -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how many pancakes the truck sold -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is an int. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because we want to use it to repeat, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "we make it identifiable...",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "...and define an ID-computed property that returns the name. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now we can create our data set as an array of pancakes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "We could load this from an external data source ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "but here we'll define it in the code. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "Besides cachapa and injera, we also add crêpe. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can make the bar chart data driven with ForEach. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, remove the second bar.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "And all we need to do now ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "is to repeat the BarMark with a ForEach.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "I pick \"element\" as the name of the variable in the loop.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we can use element.name for x...",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "...and element.sales for y.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "If ForEach is the only content in the chart, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can also put the data directly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=370"
  },
  {
    "text": "into the chart initializer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can now add the remaining three entries ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=379"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the jian bing, dosa, and american pancakes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "As we add more entries to the array, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "we add new bar marks to the chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lastly, we see that the labels ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "are becoming close to each other. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "By swapping x and y, we transpose the chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=398"
  },
  {
    "text": "and give the labels for each bar more space. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Swift Charts framework automatically chooses ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=405"
  },
  {
    "text": "an appropriate axis style to make your chart beautiful. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=408"
  },
  {
    "text": "And with that, we made our first data visualization ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "in Swift Charts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "And using the new variant feature in Xcode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can see that this chart looks beautiful in Dark Mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "adapts to different font sizes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "device sizes and orientations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "and supports accessibility.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "To access the data in a visual representation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "you need to be able to see. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts exposes the data in a visualization to VoiceOver ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that everyone can explore the details of the popular pancakes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "When I navigate the chart in VoiceOver, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "it speaks the name and number of pancakes sold. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=455"
  },
  {
    "text": "VoiceOver: Cachapa, 916. Injera, 850. Crêpes, 802. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "Jian Ping, 753. Dosa, 654. American, 618. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dominik: And of course, the chart supports ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=471"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Audio Graphs feature Apple presented in 2021, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "including the sonifications. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=476"
  },
  {
    "text": "VoiceOver: Describe chart. Chart Details. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "Play Audio Graph. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "Complete. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=488"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dominik: We just used Swift Charts to add ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "an informative and accessible chart to the food truck app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "The chart shows how many pancakes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=497"
  },
  {
    "text": "the truck sold of each style. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "Besides the summaries for each style of pancake, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=503"
  },
  {
    "text": "the food truck also has per-day sales data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=506"
  },
  {
    "text": "The truck can park in Cupertino and San Francisco. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=511"
  },
  {
    "text": "We want to help the food truck know where to park ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "on different days of the week. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "To answer this question, let's visualize the data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=520"
  },
  {
    "text": "as a time series for our two cities. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "To see how easy it is to explore different designs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "we will make three iterations of the chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=531"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will start by making a bar graph for Cupertino. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=535"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we will add the data for San Francisco and add a picker. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=540"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, we will combine the data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=546"
  },
  {
    "text": "into one multiseries line chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=548"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's start with the bar chart showing the average number ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=551"
  },
  {
    "text": "of pancakes sold per day of the week. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=554"
  },
  {
    "text": "The sales data has the weekday stored as a date ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=558"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how many pancakes the truck sold as an integer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=562"
  },
  {
    "text": "The data for Cupertino is in a variable, cupertinoData. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=567"
  },
  {
    "text": "As before, we start making a chart with a BarMark. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=573"
  },
  {
    "text": "We set the x-position of the bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=578"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be derived from the day of the date...",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=580"
  },
  {
    "text": "...and the height to be derived from the sales.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=585"
  },
  {
    "text": "And this gives us a first iteration of a chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "that shows the sales data per day of the week for Cupertino. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=594"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the second iteration, let's add the data for San Francisco. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=599"
  },
  {
    "text": "Using this chart, we want to help the pancake truck ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=604"
  },
  {
    "text": "decide where to park during the week. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=607"
  },
  {
    "text": "The sales data for San Francisco is in the sfData variable. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "We want to toggle between the two cities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=615"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see the bar chart for each city. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=618"
  },
  {
    "text": "We start with adding a state variable, city. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=620"
  },
  {
    "text": "And then we add a SwiftUI picker for the city to the View.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "To toggle between the sales summaries for the two cities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=635"
  },
  {
    "text": "via the city variable, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "we add a switch statement for the data variable.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=640"
  },
  {
    "text": "And all we have to do now is to replace the data for Cupertino ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=648"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the one that toggles between the two -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=652"
  },
  {
    "text": "Cupertino and San Francisco. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=654"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I switch the toggle, the charts toggles ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=659"
  },
  {
    "text": "between the two cities. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts works with SwiftUI animations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=663"
  },
  {
    "text": "so if we specify that the transition should be animated ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=667"
  },
  {
    "text": "with easeInOut, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=670"
  },
  {
    "text": "the bars animate as I toggle between the two cities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=671"
  },
  {
    "text": "and also only shows one location at a time.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=676"
  },
  {
    "text": "This gives our app the right look and feel. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=681"
  },
  {
    "text": "As our final iteration, we will show both series ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=685"
  },
  {
    "text": "in a line chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=688"
  },
  {
    "text": "To make this line chart, we start with the bar chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=691"
  },
  {
    "text": "from Cupertino from before. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=694"
  },
  {
    "text": "The data for Cupertino and San Francisco ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=696"
  },
  {
    "text": "is in an array of series. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "Series structs have the city and sales data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=701"
  },
  {
    "text": "Before we show both series, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=706"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's focus on the Cupertino data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the chart, we can loop over the series data. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=713"
  },
  {
    "text": "Remember, the chart initializer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "acts just like a ForEach.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=719"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we can replace the specific data for Cupertino ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=723"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the sales data from the series.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=727"
  },
  {
    "text": "To distinguish the data for the two cities, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "I want the color of the bars to be derived from the city. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=735"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this, we set the foregroundStyle ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=739"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be derived from the city in the series.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=741"
  },
  {
    "text": "To show what city a color represents, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=747"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts creates a legend below the chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=749"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, I add the data for the second location.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see in the preview, Swift Charts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=757"
  },
  {
    "text": "automatically chooses a color for San Francisco, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=759"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it shows the bars for both cities in the chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=762"
  },
  {
    "text": "Charts show data for a particular context ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=767"
  },
  {
    "text": "and a visualization may need to change ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "as our data or questions change. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=771"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts makes it easy to quickly change your chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=775"
  },
  {
    "text": "to explore different designs. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=779"
  },
  {
    "text": "The stacked bar chart is great ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "for showing the total average sales per day; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=783"
  },
  {
    "text": "but what if I wanted to do a comparison ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=786"
  },
  {
    "text": "between the two cities? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=788"
  },
  {
    "text": "Maybe a point or line chart would be better. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=790"
  },
  {
    "text": "We change the mark type from a BarMark to a PointMark ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=794"
  },
  {
    "text": "to display the pancakes sold as points, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=798"
  },
  {
    "text": "or to a LineMark to show the data as a line chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=801"
  },
  {
    "text": "A line chart is a good fit for the sales data ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=805"
  },
  {
    "text": "since it lets us compare the two cities in each day of the week. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=808"
  },
  {
    "text": "Charts can combine multiple marks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=813"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, I can add a PointMark.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=815"
  },
  {
    "text": "To make the series differentiable without color, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=824"
  },
  {
    "text": "we set the symbol to be derived from the city.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=826"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now each point indicates the city by its color and symbol. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=836"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because it is common to show points on a line, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=841"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts has a shorthand for this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=843"
  },
  {
    "text": "where we apply the symbol modifier to the LineMark. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=845"
  },
  {
    "text": "The style of the points adapts to the line. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=849"
  },
  {
    "text": "This chart is great. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=853"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can easily compare the sales trends throughout the week. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=855"
  },
  {
    "text": "We observe that the sales are especially high ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=859"
  },
  {
    "text": "in San Francisco on Sundays. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=861"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts made it very easy for us ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=864"
  },
  {
    "text": "to iterate through many designs in just a few minutes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=866"
  },
  {
    "text": "So to wrap up, let's look at how Swift Charts makes it easy ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=871"
  },
  {
    "text": "to iterate quickly and at the same time be flexible enough ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=875"
  },
  {
    "text": "to seamlessly integrate charts into your app's unique style. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=879"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Swift Charts, you build charts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=883"
  },
  {
    "text": "by composition of marks with mark properties. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=885"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the Pancake app, we composed charts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=890"
  },
  {
    "text": "with three different marks and four mark properties. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=892"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, we made a simple bar chart ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=897"
  },
  {
    "text": "as a bar mark with x and y properties. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=900"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also changed the mark to quickly explore designs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=905"
  },
  {
    "text": "like charts with points, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=908"
  },
  {
    "text": "or line charts where we used the line mark ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=911"
  },
  {
    "text": "with x and y properties.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=913"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also saw that we can add properties, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=918"
  },
  {
    "text": "like Foreground Style, to show multiple series in a line chart. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=921"
  },
  {
    "text": "And a chart doesn't have to have just one mark. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=927"
  },
  {
    "text": "We combined points and lines, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=930"
  },
  {
    "text": "and showed the same value with two mark properties. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=935"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts supports even more marks and mark properties ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=940"
  },
  {
    "text": "than we used today. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=944"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's also extensible and you can add custom marks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=946"
  },
  {
    "text": "Marks and mark properties is what allows Swift Charts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=951"
  },
  {
    "text": "to express a wide range of chart designs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=954"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a small number of declarative building blocks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=957"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are many ways in which you can combine ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=962"
  },
  {
    "text": "these building block to create great data visualizations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=963"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=966"
  },
  {
    "text": "Together with what you can already do in SwiftUI, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=969"
  },
  {
    "text": "the possibilities are truly endless. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=972"
  },
  {
    "text": "And as I've showed you today, you get support for Dark Mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=976"
  },
  {
    "text": "different device screen sizes, Dynamic Type, VoiceOver, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=979"
  },
  {
    "text": "and Audio Graphs for free. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=983"
  },
  {
    "text": "In addition, Swift Charts supports High-Contrast mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=986"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, Swift Charts works across locales ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=991"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is multiplatform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=994"
  },
  {
    "text": "The chart with the same code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=997"
  },
  {
    "text": "works across all Apple platforms. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=998"
  },
  {
    "text": "And the same customizations work everywhere ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1001"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can tailor the chart to each platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1003"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, I showed you how Swift Charts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1007"
  },
  {
    "text": "uses SwiftUI's powerful compositional syntax ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1010"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can make more charts with less code. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1013"
  },
  {
    "text": "Swift Charts also provides ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1017"
  },
  {
    "text": "a rich set of customization options, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1018"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can style the chart to match your application. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1020"
  },
  {
    "text": "And now that you know how to chart new territory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1025"
  },
  {
    "text": "and make a chart, you can learn how to customize it in the docs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1027"
  },
  {
    "text": "and in our follow-up talk where you'll raise the bar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1030"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-10136/?time=1033"
  }
]